tplinkStackMIB.name: tplinkStackMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tplinkStackMIB.description: This MIB module contain a collection of managed objects that apply to network devices with stack function.

tpStackName.name: tpStackName
tpStackName.description: An unique tag for the stack system.

tpStackMacAddress.name: tpStackMacAddress
tpStackMacAddress.description: The mac address the stack uses to communicate with other devices.

tpStackTopo.name: tpStackTopo
tpStackTopo.description: The current topo state of the stack.

tpStackAuthMode.name: tpStackAuthMode
tpStackAuthMode.description: The authentication mode used in stack creation.

tpStackAuthKey.name: tpStackAuthKey
tpStackAuthKey.description: The password to be used in stack authentication if the Stack Auth Mode is Simple or Md5.

tpSwitchInfoTable.name: tpSwitchInfoTable
tpSwitchInfoTable.description: This table contains information specific to switches in a stack.

tpSwitchInfoEntry.name: tpSwitchInfoEntry
tpSwitchInfoEntry.description: A conceptual row in the switchInfoTable describing a switch information.

tpSwitchCurrentUnit.name: tpSwitchCurrentUnit
tpSwitchCurrentUnit.description: This object contains the current switch identification number.

tpSwitchDesignatedUnit.name: tpSwitchDesignatedUnit
tpSwitchDesignatedUnit.description: This object contains the preferred unit number for the switch. auto: When this option is selected, the device will be assigned a free unit number automatically. unit-x: When this option is selected, the device will try to obtain unit-x first,treated as auto when it is not available to obtain a preffered unit number.

tpSwitchRole.name: tpSwitchRole
tpSwitchRole.description: This object describes the function of the switch: slave - stack member. master - stack master.

tpSwitchPriority.name: tpSwitchPriority
tpSwitchPriority.description: A number containing the priority of a switch. The switch with the highest priority will become the master.

tpSwitchMacAddress.name: tpSwitchMacAddress
tpSwitchMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the switch.

tpSwitchVersion.name: tpSwitchVersion
tpSwitchVersion.description: The software version of the switch.

tpSwitchState.name: tpSwitchState
tpSwitchState.description: The current state of a switch: init - The switch is initializing. disc - The switch is discovering other switchs. sync - The switch is now synchronizing config with other stack members. ready - The switch is now ready. verMismatch - The software version running on the master is different with this member.

tpStackPortInfoTable.name: tpStackPortInfoTable
tpStackPortInfoTable.description: This table contains stackport specific information. There exists an entry in this table for every physical stack port that have an entry in the ifTable (IF-MIB).

tpStackPortInfoEntry.name: tpStackPortInfoEntry
tpStackPortInfoEntry.description: A conceptual row in the stackPortInfoTable. An entry contains information about a stackport.

tpStackPortEnable.name: tpStackPortEnable
tpStackPortEnable.description: Whether the port is enable as a stack port. disable - Ethernet port mode. enable - Stack port mode.

tpStackPortStatus.name: tpStackPortStatus
tpStackPortStatus.description: The state of the stackport. ok - Connected and operational. down - Link down. authFail - The stack port is link-up but no discovery packets received or malformed packet received. ethernet - The port now works in Ethernet mode.

tpStackPortNeighbor.name: tpStackPortNeighbor
tpStackPortNeighbor.description: The mac address of the switch directly links on the stack port.
